cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.NA. 

The paper discusses a methodology for motion planning, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The algorithm involves numerical optimization and approximation techniques (cs.NA) and deals with the manipulation of geometric objects (cs.CG). The use of boxes and their connectivity also suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
